http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title.value: Indiana Academic Standards for Health & Wellness

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: The updated Indiana Academic Standards for Health & Wellness were approved unanimously by the Indiana State Board of Education on October 3, 2007. Work on the standards began in 2006 with a review of the 2002 Indiana Health Education Standards; and standards used by other state departments of education. The standards were updated for all grades, K – 12, and were aligned to the 2007 National Health Education Standards. Early drafts of the updated standards were reviewed by teachers, community health educators and university health education faculty. The standards were also posted online for review by Indiana teachers, administrators, school nurses, parents, physicians and community members. In the final step, the updated standards were again reviewed by national content reviewers for content, rigor, specificity, and comprehensiveness.
Students will comprehend concepts related to health promotion and disease prevention to enhance health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Students acknowledge personal responsibility for health promotion and/or risk reduction. They describe healthy behaviors to prevent or reduce their risk of injury and/or illness. Students list the components of health as emotional, physical and social.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Name healthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify that physical health is one dimension of health and wellness.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Identify that a healthy person exercises, eats well, and goes to the doctor.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Tell ways to prevent the spread of germs.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Tell about self-care routines that can help prevent illness and infectious diseases.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: State behaviors to prevent or reduce childhood injuries.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Tell peers how to play safely on the playground to prevent injuries.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Tell why it is important to be checked by a doctor or dentist.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: State the benefits of going to the doctor and/or dentist.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Tell how healthy behaviors impact personal health and wellness.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Tell why being tobacco-free is a healthy behavior.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Identify words that describe emotions and relate common emotions to situations.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain the steps of the universal precautions (don't touch another person's bodily fluids, don't pick up needles, etc.).

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify places to play to prevent common childhood injuries.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Explain why it is important to have regular medical checkups.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain that doctors and nurses have special skills, knowledge and equipment to detect and care for health problems.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify that healthy behaviors affect personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe that exercising, healthy eating, and being tobacco-free can help keep the body strong and healthy.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Recognize that there are multiple dimensions of health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Identify the dimensions of health as physical, mental and social.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe ways to prevent communicable diseases.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe methods for preventing the spread of germs through food, water, air, and touch.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: List ways to prevent common childhood injuries.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: List safety rules and safety equipment to use that help make playing sports activities safe.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe why it is important to seek health care.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe the importance of regular dental visits, physical exams, immunizations, and eye exams, etc.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify the link between healthy choices and being healthy.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Cite how choosing to avoid tobacco use can impact personal health (e.g., prevents tobacco-related bad breath and discoloring of teeth, prevents tobacco burns on clothing and furniture, reduced risk of pre-cancerous mouth lesions).

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Give examples of physical and emotional health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain how exercising, eating well and getting enough sleep helps people feel better emotionally when they experience stressful times.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify how a safe and healthy school environment promotes personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Tell in your own words how the school supports healthy eating behaviors.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify ways to prevent common childhood injuries.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Identify safety measures and equipment to prevent accidents and injuries in the home (e.g., burns, falls, cuts, etc.).

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Recognize times when it might be important to seek health care.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Recognize that symptoms like a fever, sore throat, or tooth- ache might need to be detected and treated by going to a health care provider.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Explain the connection between behaviors and personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain that refraining from tobacco use can prevent nicotine addiction.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Recognize examples of intellectual and social health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain ways that healthy relationships, with family members and friends, contribute to positive social health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Give examples of how rules against smoking on school property and public places protect others from the effects of environmental tobacco smoke.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Explain ways to prevent common health problems.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain safety rules and equipment to reduce the risk of swimming injuries and drowning.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Explain how to prevent illness by seeking care from medical personnel.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain that a health care provider can give immunizations to help prevent diseases during childhood and adolescence.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe the relationship between healthy behaviors and personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain that refraining from tobacco use can prevent damage to the body.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify examples of emotional, intellectual, physical, and social health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain that feeling good about oneself and being able to identify what makes one unique and special are signs of positive emotional health and wellness.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe ways in which a safe and healthy school and community environment can promote personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain how bike paths, walking trails, sidewalks, playgrounds, and safe places to play can promote physical activity.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe ways to prevent common childhood injuries and health problems.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe how to prevent the spread of cold and flu viruses.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe when it is important to seek health care.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe common signs and symptoms of diseases and/or disorders and when to seek the care of medical, dental, mental/emotional, or other health-care providers.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Compare how healthy behaviors and personal health are linked.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Compare and contrast ways to resist pressure to use alcohol, tobacco or other drugs and the result of implementing such techniques.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify the interrelationships of emotional and social health in adolescence.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Identify how having positive relationships with others help develop a positive self-concept.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Examine how one's surroundings impact health and wellness.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify how family culture or beliefs can impact personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Identify the different ways that families cope with stress (from change, crisis, rejection, loss, and separation) and how it impacts personal health.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: List ways to reduce or prevent injuries.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: List the equipment and safety steps to use when participating in any wheeled sport activity.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify how health care can promote health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Identify healthcare products and good personal hygiene practices that promote personal health for adolescents.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify the benefits of practicing healthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Cite the benefits of daily dental care (e.g., brushing, flossing, visits to a dentist, etc.)

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe the likelihood of injuries or illnesses if engaging in unhealthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe the short and long-term health effects of tobacco use and/or discuss choices that could lead to incidences of conflict, harassment, bullying, and vandalism and the potential results.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Examine how healthy behaviors influence personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Examine the results of a personal fitness plan and the importance of exercise in maintaining optimal health and wellness.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Summarize the interrelationships of emotional, social and physical health in adolescence.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Illustrate how family change (e.g., moving, divorce, addiction, death, etc.) can impact emotional, social and physical health of an adolescent.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Discover how the environment can impact personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Recognize environmental conditions (e.g., physical, social, community, etc.) that are potentially harmful to personal health.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Cite how family heredity can impact personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Cite hereditary diseases and/or disorders prevalent among various ethnic groups that can impact personal health and wellness.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Explain ways to reduce or prevent health risks among adolescents.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain that by not having body piercing and tattooing the risk of bacterial infections and lifelong diseases such as hepatitis and HIV infection can be prevented and/or reduced.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe how immediate health care can promote individual health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe first aid procedures to promote personal health (e.g., first aid care for respiratory and cardiac emergencies, cold and heat emergencies, bone and joint injuries, and other medical emergencies).

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Determine the barriers to practicing healthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Determine the barriers to good nutrition at home, school and in social situations.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Predict the risk of injury or illness if engaging in unhealthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Predict the short- and long-term physical and social health effects of alcohol and other drug use.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Analyze the relationship between healthy behaviors and personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Investigate the relationship of engaging in regular physical activity and healthy eating to maintain and/or enhance personal health.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe the interrelationships of emotional, intellectual, physical, and social health in adolescence.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe the health-related factors that early sexual behaviors can have on the emotional, physical and social health of adolescents.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Analyze how the environment impacts personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Analyze the environmental health conditions of diverse countries and how it can impact personal health.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe how family history can impact personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe how heredity, family dietary behaviors and the mental and emotional health of family environments can impact the quality of life and health.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe ways to reduce or prevent adolescent health problems and injuries .

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe that abstinence from sexual behaviors can prevent pregnancy, sexually transmitted infections and HIV/AIDS.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Explain how appropriate health care can promote personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Determine when treatment of illness is appropriate at home or when and how to seek further medical help when needed.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe the benefits of and barriers to practicing healthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe health behaviors that reduce the risk of cardiovascular disease and identify barriers for practicing these behaviors.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Examine the likelihood of injury or illness if engaging in unhealthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Examine the potential health risks related to one or more of the following behaviors (e.g., physical inactivity, sexual activity, tobacco use, alcohol or other drug use, violence, etc.).

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Examine the potential seriousness of injury or illness if engaging in unhealthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Examine how body piercing, tattooing, and IV drug use can increase one's risk of bacterial infections and lifelong diseases such as hepatitis and HIV infection.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Document how personal behaviors can impact health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Document the impact of personal health behaviors on heart health.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Explain the interrelationships of emotional, social and physical health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain the relationship between a physical health impairment and an individual's emotional and social health.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Examine how the environment and health are connected.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Draw conclusions on how environmental health issues can impact the personal health of children or the elderly.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Examine the impact that genetics can have on personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Examine personal health-related actions that can reduce the risk and/or delay the onset of potential genetic and family health problems.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Formulate ways to prevent or reduce the risk of health problems.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Identify and develop approaches to educate peers (adolescents) about risk reduction (e.g., teen pregnancy, suicide, bullying, abuse, etc.).

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Investigate the connection between access to health care and health status.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Compare and contrast the relationship of immunization policies and availability of health care on the health status of children in other countries.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Summarize the benefits and barriers to practicing healthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Construct a list of practices to reduce and/or prevent stress and identify ways to overcome barriers.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Predict susceptibility to injury or illness if engaging in unhealthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Investigate adolescent risk behaviors which could lead to injury or illness.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Discover the severity of illness if engaging in unhealthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Recognize health behaviors which increase the risk of Avian Influenza / Pandemic Flu transmission in developing countries.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Predict how healthy behaviors can impact health status.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Predict how maintaining healthy behaviors throughout life can have an impact on quality of life and longevity.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe the interrelationships of emotional, intellectual, physical and social health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe how aspects of health are interrelated and may be affected by disease, illness, injury, broken relationships, etc.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Analyze how environment and personal health are interrelated.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Compare and contrast the short and long-term impact that natural disasters can have on personal health and how community health organizations can intervene.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Analyze how genetics and family history can affect personal health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Analyze a specific genetic disorder in a family tree and the impact it has on personal health and health behaviors to reduce the risk.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Propose ways to reduce or prevent injuries and health problems.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Propose new rules and regulations to reduce or prevent vehicle crashes and injuries.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Analyze the relationship between access to health care and health status.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Examine the changes in the health status of individuals as a result of improved health care offered in the United States and/or other countries.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Compare and contrast the benefits of and barriers to practicing a variety of healthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Compare and contrast the benefits of and barriers to belonging to a health club or implementing a personal fitness plan at home.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Analyze personal susceptibility to injury, illness or death if engaging in unhealthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Analyze the personal health risks associated with tobacco, alcohol and other drug use.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Analyze the potential severity of injury or illness if engaging in unhealthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Research the health-related behaviors which impact the risk of HIV / AIDS transmission.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Students will analyze the influence of family, peers, culture, media, technology and other factors on health behaviors.
Identify how the family influences personal health practices.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Name the health practices of family members observed (e.g., brushing teeth, washing hands, wearing safety belt, looking both ways before crossing a street, etc.), and/or name physical activities in which you have observed family members participating (e.g., mowing the yard, working in the garden, running on treadmill, bicycling, playing kickball, etc.).

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Recall the school guidelines for communicating feelings to others (e.g., use I messages such as: I feel angry, I am sad, my feelings are hurt, I am happy, etc.), and how the rules were communicated (e.g., posters, verbalized, counselor presentation, role play, etc.).

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: State how the media influences behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Name the words (e.g., slogans, rhymes, jingles, etc.) used in commercials to sell a food item, and how they can influence an individual to purchase the product.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe how the family influences personal health behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe how a family member models healthy behaviors (e.g., eating healthy foods, wearing safety equipment, going to the dentist, etc.), and/or state the physical activities that a family does together and how this influences the health of family members.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Recognize what the school can do to support personal health behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Recognize how the school counselor can help when a conflict occurs on the playground.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify how the media can influence health.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Identify how television commercials and magazine advertisements entice someone to purchase food products.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify how the family influences personal health practices and behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain how a family member teaches a child about health habits (e.g., exercise together, how to properly use safety belts, etc.), and/or tell, in your own words, the physical activities that family members do individually or together to enhance their health and wellness.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify what the school can do to support personal health practices and behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe how the peer mediation program helps to resolve conflicts on the playground.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe how the media can influence health behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe how a nutrition-related media message can entice a person to buy that food item.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Recall how the family influences personal health and wellness practices.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Show the safety practices that family members demonstrate to stay safe in the home (e.g., holding a ladder, using hand tools safely, practicing home fire drills, etc.).

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Observe the influence of culture on health practices.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Recognize the differences in health practices of different ethnic groups (e.g., medical care, hygiene practices, etc.).

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: State how peers can influence healthy behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Tell ways to invite or include peers when playing during recess or after school (playing kickball, soccer, softball, etc.).

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Discuss how the school can support personal health behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Discuss how physical education teachers encourage children to be physically active.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify how media and technology influence health behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Identify media messages depicting healthy behaviors and/or name the positive and negative impact of computers, video games, TV, pedometers, etc., on personal health and wellness.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe how the family influences personal health and behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Summarize the most common ways healthy behaviors are learned from the family.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Draw and label meals from different cultures (identifying specific geographic regions and availability of foods).

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Determine how peers can influence unhealthy behaviors and promote wellness.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Give examples of how peers can influence an inactive peer to be more physically active (e.g., play with them, invite them to join a game, identify their strength or skill).

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify how the community can support personal health practices.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: List ways the community provides opportunities for children to participate in physical activities.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe how media and technology can influence health behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Describe how the media sends mixed messages about health and wellness to children (e.g., eat heart healthy foods vs. buy these great tasting potato chips) and/or name the positive and negative impact of computers, video games, TV, pedometers, etc.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe how the family influences personal health practices and behaviors.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Identify safety equipment and safe practices that family members use when engaged in camping, boating, ice skating, skiing, and using all-terrain vehicles.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain how the school and community support physical activities through physical education class, recess, intramural sports, community parks, bicycle/walking paths and trails, and skate parks, etc.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: Explain the techniques (e.g., marketing approaches, logos, slogans, messages, environment/settings, etc.) that media uses to impact a person's thoughts, feelings or health behaviors.
